Manganese Deficiency

Photosynthesis

Phosphorus
Phosphorus is a crucial nutrient in several contexts. It is fundamentally recognized as a nutrient, and more specifically, an essential nutrient for plant growth. As such, it is a major nutrient for plants. Phosphorus is a component of chemical fertilizers and PROMOTE. Plants obtain phosphorus from the soil, a process often aided by Mycorrhiza. Bio-fertilizers also play a role in converting phosphorus into forms that plants can readily utilize. The Bio Triple Action Program can dissolve Phosphorus. Phosphorus is also provided by fertilizers.

Nitrogen
Nitrogen is a crucial nutrient utilized in various agricultural and biological contexts. It is a fundamental element provided to plants, often through fertilizers, where it is available in chemical forms. Nitrogen is recognized as one of the major nutrients essential for robust plant growth and development.

In addition to fertilizers, nitrogen can also be sourced and stabilized through biological processes, particularly by N-Factor bacteria. Furthermore, nitrogen plays a key role as a primary nutrient in products like FLOWMIN. A specific method, the Bio Triple Action Program, is used to collect nitrogen from the air, illustrating the diverse ways in which this essential element is acquired and utilized.
